# shadcn/ui in tally-crm

## Setup (from components.json)
- **Style**: new-york
- **RSC**: true
- **Base color**: zinc, CSS variables enabled
- **Aliases**: `@/components`, `@/components/ui`, `@/lib/utils`, `@/lib`, `@/hooks`

## Usage
- Use existing shadcn components from `@/components/ui/` (button, input, calendar, card, badge, icon) instead of building new primitives.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional Tailwind classes.
- Add new shadcn components via CLI: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` â€” do not copy-paste from the docs into random paths.

## Custom vs shadcn
- **Custom components** (e.g. `components/Button/Button.tsx`, `components/Select/Select.tsx`) may wrap or compose shadcn; prefer them when they encode app-specific behavior or design.
- **New UI primitives** (forms, dialogs, dropdowns) should generally be added as shadcn components to `components/ui/` for consistency.
